The paper deals with the problem of learning model initialization for neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The use of meta-learning and the proposed Chameleon model suggest a focus on deep learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The experiments involve real-life datasets, which could suggest a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) or natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the use of neural networks and the focus on learning suggest a possible fit with the neural networks subcategory (cs.NE).
